The workflow starts with: "bash subpopulation.sh".
A seperate directory is created for the all output files.
The workflow requires a directory containing the .sam input files and a target list in the following format: 

TNR=1 CHR=chr1 START=156627319 END=156627608
TNR=2 CHR=chr1 START=169555901 END=169556074
TNR=3 CHR=chr2 START=236401756 END=236402053
.
.
.

Furthermore: 
-) gawk has to be installed: sudo apt-get install gawk
-) Perl module "Switch" is required: sudo apt-get install libswitch-perl or cpan; install Switch
